      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, especially when they start pale, is a classic sign of a few things, like a nutrient deficiency or perhaps overwatering. It's a common issue, though, and you can usually fix it with a little attention. I'd suggest checking your soil moisture first; if it's soggy, let it dry out a bit, or you might need to gently repot them if the drainage is poor. Sometimes, a gentle application of a balanced fertilizer can help kickstart things, but be careful not to overdo it, or you'll just make the problem worse!",
